reviewText:
I checked the reviews and most I saw were bad. I should have listened and NOT buy this game, I wanted to give it the benefit of the doubt but was just disappointed in the end.

No players in multiplayer
Very few zombie spawns and when you do find em they spawn a min after you kill em.
Loot spawns every min on the ground. Though it'd be better if the loot comes from zombies or from stuff inside buildings
Class selection. In a survival game? Are you insane? I understand that it's mixed with action but I didn't expect it to be like that.
Those who said this game was like a cheaper version of Rust was a lie, I don't technically have the game yet or played it myself but I watched Bob and Markiplier play this and it was far better than this crap.
You glitch through an invisible hole on the ground and gets you stuck for a good 2 mins.
I like the textures I admit but the rest is just awful.
You can't even climb the stairs and just fall off when you get to the top.

I'm done.
Play Unturned, it's free, better and more fun than this game.
This game is not worth it.
But if you want to sate your curiousity then be my guest. But don't say I didn't tell you so.

reviewText: I bought this game because of two reasons. One, it was only $0.59. And two, I couldn't hold in my curiosity after seeing the many creative reviews. I didn't even care enough to make a desktop shortcut when it asked me to. While I created my character I picked the first model I saw just to get away from the laggy menu screen. I loaded into a desert, I imedietly noticed the great world design. Then I moved. I was suprised with the amount of lag, I thought that it wouldn't have any lag since it doesn't even need 2GB of RAM to run. After puting 6 minutes into the game I would like for two things to change. One, more graphics choices. And two, an option the kill yourself in-game. 2/5, has potential.

reviewText:
How should I start this...
Should you be looking for a game to emulate that pre-alpha experience, this game is perfect for you!

We decided to have a go at this game, and it was misery from start to finish. The Let's Play we planned, turned into a review, or in this case: a general warning against paying anything for this game.

Pros
- You get to test Steam Refund.
- Large maps.

Cons
Everything else, such as:
- Dying when jumping over rocks and climbing ladders.
- Spawning beneath the world.
- Blinking textures.
- Missing walls and floors in buildings.
- ..and so on.

If you are interested in our experience with this game, check it out here:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_Mnodtti3Ns

reviewText:
I was laughing at this game with my friends, thinking it was fake from the trailer and it looked bad and all that, so I bought it just for fun. It turns out to be an OK game. There's still alot the developer(s) need to fix and add to the game. Here are just a few of things that I think should be fixed/added:

-Pickaxe
-Mining to get metal fragments
-Furnaces to smelt ores to get metal fragments from
-Pictures of the items in your inventory
-Fix picking up items (As of now you have to look for a while to find the spot on which you can pick it up from)
-Ground clipping and glitching
-Loot inside of buildings

Other than that I think it's a pretty cool game to be honest. The game doesn't require alot to run which is kinda cool, and I think it's funny that the arms, weapons and buildings you place yourself is unturned-like.
At this state i would rate this game 6/10, but if a few things that I mentioned would get added I would rate it higher.
